<h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 leading-tight">Managed Office vs Coworking Space Mumbai: <span class="text-brand-electric">Which Is Right for Your Business?</span></h1>
<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">Both managed offices and coworking spaces offer flexible alternatives to traditional leases. But they serve very different types of businesses. This guide breaks down the real differences — cost, privacy, scalability, and when each makes sense — so you can choose with confidence.</p>
</div>

<div class="glass-card p-8 lg:p-12 mb-12 reveal">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Quick Answer: The Main Difference</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">A <strong>coworking space</strong> is a shared office where multiple companies work side by side, sharing desks, meeting rooms, and common areas. You rent a desk or small cabin within a larger shared floor. A <strong>managed office</strong> is a private, dedicated space that is fully set up and maintained for your company alone — your brand, your layout, your team. Nobody else walks in.</p>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">If you need <strong>privacy, brand identity, and a space that feels like your own</strong>, a managed office is the right choice. If you need <strong>a desk for 2–5 people with minimal commitment</strong>, coworking might work. But once you hit 10+ employees, the economics and experience shift heavily in favour of managed offices.</p>
</div>

