<div class="mb-12 lg:mb-16 reveal">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">When to Choose a Managed Office</h2>
<div class="space-y-6">
<div class="glass-card p-8">
<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Your team is 10+ people and growing</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Once you pass 10 employees, coworking starts feeling cramped. Meeting rooms get booked out, phone calls happen in corridors, and your team loses the sense of having "their" space. A managed office gives you a dedicated floor where everyone belongs to one company. The per-seat cost actually drops as you scale, making it more economical than coworking at this size.</p>
</div>
<div class="glass-card p-8">
<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">You need a professional client-facing environment</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">If clients, investors, or partners visit your office regularly, a managed office projects credibility. Your name on the door, your reception area, your meeting rooms — it signals that you are an established business. Coworking spaces, despite their amenities, always feel shared and transient.</p>
</div>
<div class="glass-card p-8">
<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">You want your own culture and workplace identity</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Your office layout, break area, wall art, and even the way desks are arranged — these shape your company culture. In a managed office, you design the space around how your team actually works. In coworking, you adapt to someone else's layout.</p>
</div>
<div class="glass-card p-8">
<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">You want predictable costs without hidden charges</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Managed offices include everything — rent, furniture, internet, housekeeping, maintenance — in one per-seat monthly cost. Coworking spaces often add charges for meeting room usage, printing, guest passes, and after-hours access. With a managed office, what you see is what you pay.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="mb-12 lg:mb-16 reveal">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">When Coworking Makes Sense</h2>
<div class="space-y-6">
<div class="glass-card p-8">
<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">You are a solo founder or team of 1–5</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">For very small teams, coworking is genuinely cost-effective. You get a desk, internet, and a professional address without any setup hassle. If you are testing an idea or running a small remote team that occasionally needs a base, coworking works well.</p>
</div>
<div class="glass-card p-8">
<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">You need maximum flexibility with zero commitment</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">If your team size is uncertain or you need a temporary Mumbai base for a project, coworking offers month-to-month flexibility that managed offices typically do not match. You can walk in and walk out with minimal notice.</p>
</div>
<div class="glass-card p-8">
<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Networking with other startups is a priority</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Coworking spaces naturally create opportunities to meet other founders, freelancers, and small teams. If cross-company networking is part of your strategy, the shared environment can be valuable. Managed offices are private by design, so this serendipity does not happen.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

