<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mt-6">Notice the pattern: at small team sizes, coworking is cheaper. But as you scale past 30–50 employees, the <strong>per-seat cost of a managed office becomes competitive or even lower</strong> — and you get a private, branded space instead of sharing with strangers. The value gap widens further when you factor in meeting room availability, brand perception, and team productivity.</p>
</div>

<div class="mb-12 lg:mb-16 reveal">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">The Hybrid Approach: What Many Mumbai Companies Do</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Some companies start with coworking for their founding team and transition to a managed office once they cross 15–20 employees. This is a sensible path if you are growing fast.</p>
<p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Others run a <strong>hybrid model</strong> — a managed office as their headquarters, with a few coworking memberships for remote team members or satellite teams in different parts of Mumbai. This gives you the best of both worlds: a professional HQ and flexible satellite presence.</p>
